ca.forklabs.javaxpcom.util
Class XPCOMInspector

java.lang.Object
  ca.forklabs.javaxpcom.util.XPCOMInspector

public class XPCOMInspector
extends Object

Class XPCOMInspector is a rudimentary set of methods to inspect nsIDOMNodes. The main inspection entry point is inspect(nsIDOMNode) for a non-recursive inspection and its two-parameter sibling to control the recursion into child nodes.

inspect

public static void inspect(org.mozilla.interfaces.nsIDOMNode node)
Inspect only the node. It calls, in order, inspectNodeType(nsIDOMNode), inspectNodeNames(nsIDOMNode), inspectAttributes(nsIDOMNode) and inspectChildren(nsIDOMNode, boolean).

Parameters:
node - the node to inspect.

inspect

public static void inspect(org.mozilla.interfaces.nsIDOMNode node,
                           boolean recursive)
Inspect the node. It calls, in order, inspectNodeType(nsIDOMNode), inspectNodeNames(nsIDOMNode), inspectAttributes(nsIDOMNode) and inspectChildren(nsIDOMNode, boolean).

Parameters:
node - the node to inspect.
recursive - true to also inspect the children, then their children, depth-first; false otherwise.
